# CODEOWNERS — require explicit owner review on the security-critical
# surfaces of the backend. GitHub uses the LAST matching pattern, so
# order matters: the default owner line is first, narrow rules last.
#
# Rationale (Stage 7, P4.3 / Stage 6 §6.9.3): the auth, middleware, and
# server-wire-up layers are where a single silent regression can unlock
# unauthenticated access, break rate limiting, or disable CSRF defense.
# CODEOWNERS forces a second pair of eyes — even on a solo repo this
# creates an audit trail and a GitHub review requirement that survives
# future contributors.

# Default owner — every file has a fallback reviewer.
